Sentencas: Ba0.9Co0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-delta (BCFN), a promising cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells, demonstrates excellent activity to oxygen reduction reaction.
Titulo: Chromium deposition and poisoning on Ba0.9Co0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-δ cathode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: However, under realistic operation conditions, cathode of cells often suffers from severe degradation due to the Cr deposition and poisoning from interconnects.
Titulo: Chromium deposition and poisoning on Ba0.9Co0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-δ cathode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this work, effect of Cr deposition and poisoning on BCFN cathode has been investigated by various analysis techniques.
Titulo: Chromium deposition and poisoning on Ba0.9Co0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-δ cathode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Thereinto, temperature condition plays a significant role and BCFN demonstrate good stability at lower temperature (650 degrees C and 700 degrees C).
Titulo: Chromium deposition and poisoning on Ba0.9Co0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-δ cathode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: However, polarization resistance of BCFN increases remarkably over 750 degrees C.
Titulo: Chromium deposition and poisoning on Ba0.9Co0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-δ cathode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: According to the analysis, BaCrO4 are produced during the Cr deposition process, suppressing the oxygen reduction reaction on BCFN cathode.
Titulo: Chromium deposition and poisoning on Ba0.9Co0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-δ cathode of solid oxide fuel cells
